Massachusetts Governor Michael Dukakis,a newcomer to national politics, ended weeks of speculationwith the announcement he plans to seek the 1988 Democraticpresidential nomination.    Dukakis said he had authorized the formation of apresidential campaign committee and would make a formalannouncement of candidacy in Boston on May 4.    The 53-year-old Dukakis is serving his third term asgovernor. He was reelected with 67 per cent of the vote lastNovember. Reuter&#3;